Reasoning: The paper deals with the transmission scheme for multiuser multiantenna downlink systems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). It also considers the impact of inter-cell interference, which is a topic of interest in the networked systems (cs.NI) and control theory (cs.SY) communities. The paper also discusses the achievable degrees of freedom (DoF) region, which is a concept commonly used in the field of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) communications (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the design of a cooperative multi-cell system, which is relevant to the field of communication networks (cs.COM).
